---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import { REPO_URL } from "../consts";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="AI policy" description="How AI tools may be used when contributing to Desktop Plus." noindex>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-20 sm:px-8">
    <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-fg-muted transition hover:text-fg">
      <Icon name="octicon:arrow-left-16" class="h-4 w-4" />
      Back to home
    </a>

    <h1 class="mt-8 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">AI policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-fg-muted">
      This policy explains how AI tools (like large language models) may be used when contributing to <a
        href={REPO_URL}
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-brand-400 underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-brand-300">Desktop Plus</a
      >.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg-muted">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Code</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          AI-generated code is allowed. However, the author takes full responsibility for its correctness. Before opening a pull request, the author
          must read all the code, understand it, and change whatever needs changing. Treat AI output as a draft you are accountable for, not as
          finished work.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Communication</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          All interaction in issues and pull requests, including descriptions and comments, must be written by a human. Two exceptions are allowed:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <Icon name="octicon:dot-fill-16" class="mt-1 h-3.5 w-3.5 shrink-0 text-brand-400" />
            <span>
              <b class="font-semibold text-fg">Translation.</b> You can use AI to translate your message into another language (usually English). The ideas
              and text must still be your own, AI is only translating them.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <Icon name="octicon:dot-fill-16" class="mt-1 h-3.5 w-3.5 shrink-0 text-brand-400" />
            <span>
              <b class="font-semibold text-fg">Quotes and technical analysis.</b> You may append a quote or an analysis produced by an LLM, as long as it
              is clearly marked. A reader must be able to tell, without any doubt, which parts are written by you and which parts come from an AI.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>

    <section class="mt-12 rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface/60 p-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg-muted">
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-2 text-base font-semibold text-white">
        <Icon name="octicon:info-16" class="h-4 w-4 text-brand-400" />
        A note about this website
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3">
        All text content on <span class="font-mono">desktop-plus.org</span> is my own (including any mistakes).
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Part of the website structure and CSS styling were vibe-coded. This may look like it contradicts the policy above, but I think it's fine here
        for the following reasons:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <Icon name="octicon:dot-fill-16" class="mt-1 h-3.5 w-3.5 shrink-0 text-brand-400" />
          <span
            >My frontend design skills are very limited. Doing this by hand would have taken weeks and the result would have been <i>much</i> worse. I'd
            rather spend my time and energy on the actual Desktop Plus app.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <Icon name="octicon:dot-fill-16" class="mt-1 h-3.5 w-3.5 shrink-0 text-brand-400" />
          <span>
            This is a fully static website, used purely for marketing, and has no impact on the app itself. If the code quality isn't great, the worst
            that can happen is that the website looks bad on some devices. Feel free to open an issue if that happens.
          </span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
